<paragraph id="8BDC369AFFFAFF95FF5DFCEBFCA52558" blockId="79.[163,779,859,1065]" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFAFF95FF5DFCEBFEBE2200" box="[163,281,860,881]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Although females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FFFAFF95FDF5FCEBFDFB2201" authorityName="Kury &amp; Ferreira" authorityYear="2012" box="[523,604,859,881]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Roquettea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="79" pageNumber="664" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peba">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFAFF95FDF5FCEBFDFB2201" box="[523,604,859,881]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">R. peba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFAFF95FD71FCEBFD062200" box="[655,673,860,881]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFFFAFF95FD71FCEBFD062200" box="[655,673,860,881]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">R</collectionCode>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FFFAFF95FD55FCECFCAD2201" authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Kury" authorityYear="2010" box="[683,778,859,880]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Roquettea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="79" pageNumber="664" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scrotalis">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFAFF95FD55FCECFCAD2201" box="[683,778,859,880]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">scrotalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not known, the colour pattern of the males shows the occurrence of yellow spots in areas of mesotergum and even the carapace. Female of 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FFFAFF95FDBBFC0FFD1922BD" authorityName="Medrano &amp; Kury &amp; Mendes" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Medrano &amp; Kury &amp; Mendes" baseAuthorityYear="1947" box="[581,702,951,973]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Gryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="79" pageNumber="664" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andina" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFAFF95FDBBFC0FFD1922BD" box="[581,702,951,973]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">R. andina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22457F3FFFAFF95FD39FC00FF68229A" pageId="79" pageNumber="664" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from its congeners by having: mesotergum almost deprived of yellow spots and ornamentation of area I extremely reduced/inconspicuous (
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFFFAFF95FD8BFBA4FD552558" box="[629,754,1043,1065]" captionStart="Figure 59" captionStartId="79.[163,243,1817,1839]" captionTargetBox="[167,775,1433,1778]" captionTargetId="figure-731@79.[167,775,1433,1778]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="Figure 59. Roquettea andina, female holotype (SMF RII 5873/10). A, dorsal view. B, oblique view. C, original label. Photos courtesy Abel Pérez." pageId="79" pageNumber="664">Fig. 59A, B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC369AFFFAFF95FF5DFBE5FC35237F" blockId="79.[163,779,1106,1373]" lastBlockId="79.[827,1444,197,526]" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFAFF95FF5DFBE5FEE22516" box="[163,325,1106,1127]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">Distribution:</emphasis>
There is no record to date of one species similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FFFAFF95FE7FFBC6FDFF25F7" authorityName="Medrano &amp; Kury &amp; Mendes" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Roewer" baseAuthorityYear="1947" box="[385,600,1137,1158]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Roquettea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="79" pageNumber="664" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andina">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFAFF95FE7FFBC6FDFF25F7" box="[385,600,1137,1158]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">Roquettea andina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Maracay (
<collectingCountry id="F374760AFFFAFF95FF55FB38FE8E25D4" box="[171,297,1167,1189]" name="Venezuela" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
). We do not have any evidence that this locality is mistaken. However, a significant similarity with other females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FFFAFF95FE39FB7AFDE32593" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1931" box="[455,580,1229,1250]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Roquettea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="79" pageNumber="664" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFAFF95FE39FB7AFDE32593" box="[455,580,1229,1250]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">Roquettea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is evident and the present analysis retrieved it nested in a clade with them. 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FFFAFF95FECFFABCFE0F2451" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1931" box="[305,424,1291,1312]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Roquettea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="79" pageNumber="664" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFAFF95FECFFABCFE0F2451" box="[305,424,1291,1312]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">Roquettea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recently revised and its distribution seems to be restricted almost uniquely to the Basin of 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F878FFFAFF95FECEFAF0FE38242C" box="[304,415,1351,1373]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">Tocantins</collectingRegion>
River, in lower 
<collectingCountry id="F374760AFFFAFF95FDAEFAF0FD31242C" box="[592,662,1351,1373]" name="Brazil" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B6BFFFAFF95FD5BFAF0FC7521AB" author="Medrano M &amp; Kury AB" box="[677,978,197,1373]" pageId="79" pageNumber="664" pagination="1206 - 1233" refId="ref53005" refString="Medrano M, Kury AB. 2018. Relationships and cladistic analysis of Roquettea with description of two new species and notes about evolution of stylus in Cosmetidae (Opiliones, Grassatores). Invertebrate Systematics 32: 1206 - 1233." type="journal article" year="2018">Medrano &amp; Kury, 2018</bibRefCitation>
), the closest point of a 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FFFAFF95FB24FF71FA0421AA" box="[1242,1443,197,219]" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFAFF95FB24FF71FAEC21AA" box="[1242,1355,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">Roquettea</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
to Maracay is near 
<quantity id="4C9B9B7FFFFAFF95FBE5FF53FB26218B" box="[1051,1153,228,250]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="79" pageNumber="664" unit="km" value="2000.0">2000 km</quantity>
, whereby we suspected a spelling error in the original label (
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFFFAFF95FB30FEB5FA892069" box="[1230,1326,258,280]" captionStart="Figure 59" captionStartId="79.[163,243,1817,1839]" captionTargetBox="[167,775,1433,1778]" captionTargetId="figure-731@79.[167,775,1433,1778]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="Figure 59. Roquettea andina, female holotype (SMF RII 5873/10). A, dorsal view. B, oblique view. C, original label. Photos courtesy Abel Pérez." pageId="79" pageNumber="664">Fig. 59C</figureCitation>
). A recent visit to 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFFFAFF95FC72FE96FC7E2047" box="[908,985,289,310]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/90vz-swjg" name="Museu Paraense Emilio Goeldi" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">MPEG</collectionCode>
by the first author allowed identification of a hitherto ‘undescribed’ species from Ilha de Marajó (with spelling suspiciously similar to Maracay) that possesses the same pattern of coloration as 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FFFAFF95FAD2FECAFA3A20E3" authorityName="Medrano &amp; Kury &amp; Mendes" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Roewer" baseAuthorityYear="1947" box="[1324,1437,381,402]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Roquettea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="79" pageNumber="664" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andina">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFAFF95FAD2FECAFA3A20E3" box="[1324,1437,381,402]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">G. andina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but we do not have access to this material at the present time. Future investigations will allow us to determine if they are, in fact, specimens of the same species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC369AFFFAFF95FCC5FD81FBCE2211" blockId="79.[827,1444,566,864]" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFAFF95FCC5FD81FC04233A" box="[827,931,566,587]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">Remarks:</emphasis>
The genus was recently revised and a cladistic analysis tested and corroborated the monophyly of 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FFFAFF95FCC5FDC3FC0D23F8" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1931" box="[827,938,628,649]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Roquettea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="79" pageNumber="664" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFAFF95FCC5FDC3FC0D23F8" box="[827,938,628,649]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">Roquettea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The inclusion of 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FFFAFF95FB8EFDC3FAAB23F8" authorityName="Medrano &amp; Kury &amp; Mendes" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Medrano &amp; Kury &amp; Mendes" baseAuthorityYear="1947" box="[1136,1292,628,649]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Gryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="79" pageNumber="664" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andina">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFAFF95FB8EFDC3FAAB23F8" box="[1136,1292,628,649]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">Gryne andina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a member of 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FFFAFF95FCA6FD24FC6C23D9" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1931" box="[856,971,659,680]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Roquettea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="79" pageNumber="664" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFAFF95FCA6FD24FC6C23D9" box="[856,971,659,680]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">Roquettea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not require the modification of the diagnosis of the genus. On the other hand, the female specimen used by Roewer in the description may be identified as a member of 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FFFAFF95FB62FD58FAB62275" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1931" box="[1180,1297,751,772]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Roquettea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="79" pageNumber="664" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFAFF95FB62FD58FAB62275" box="[1180,1297,751,772]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="664">Roquettea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by external morphology and by having the same colour pattern of small spots absent from part of mesotergum and from fenestra posterior (
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFFFAFF95FBF1FCFDFBFD2211" box="[1039,1114,842,864]" captionStart="Figure 59" captionStartId="79.[163,243,1817,1839]" captionTargetBox="[167,775,1433,1778]" captionTargetId="figure-731@79.[167,775,1433,1778]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="Figure 59. Roquettea andina, female holotype (SMF RII 5873/10). A, dorsal view. B, oblique view. C, original label. Photos courtesy Abel Pérez." pageId="79" pageNumber="664">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
